ZULU King Goodwill Zwelithini told Democratic Alliance leader Mmusi Maimane that Mzansi needs opposition parties that are not afraid to address the issues troubling the country.Zwelithini was speaking during Maimane’s visit to the Usuthu Royal Palace in Nongoma, northern KZN. The king spoke about the proposed dissolution of the Ingonyama Trust. The trust is a corporate body that owns various pieces of land in KZN and controls three million hectares of land on behalf of the king. if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");var viewReq = new Array();function vu(u) {var i=new Image();i.src=u.replace("&amp;","&");viewReq.push(i);}vu("https://securepubads.g.doubleclick.net/pcs/view?xai\x3dAKAOjsuJMbtbL8qWErIgoqMiwBG7gft_71V1IZBuRR5ZnIsH56DxnWfMzb6GSsZ878OUCplnINN_-X3siIdMWUz1CgmBbA7uTTbUSQZDxHNZLAEWv03kfdJYtfTnEedhtUDKD82ajTLwjS9r6qeveiUpRwGwaA25W0ZFrO4qv4r2B1h-ppypXBUPnH_yeR_o19BDfqzAHsbsQVr92PZedvYFFomhNITvWRPY5V2Q21IYkBj9DNrEV8xTWrwJbYJfL4LriQAgF4er_KSaNOLjo4QxhPB9_bhN3Qc\x26sig\x3dCg0ArKJSzIX1fT--mXU5EAE\x26urlfix\x3d1\x26adurl\x3d")

   
